- Expensive Shit $600,000,000 - (Artist: Robness Cyberpop)

A Robness modern masterpiece that remixes the most valuable art of the past whilst acknowledging a half century's worth of sampling, nostalgic and modern art. This timeless digital blockchain art piece unabashedly looks towards the future by reassembling art's prestigious history in a new techno-optimist perspective.

This is one of the many 'Save Hollywood' pieces in the series.  This one can be found on KnownOrigin and the list price is above.  It is my 2nd most favorite piece besides 'Highway Slut' which is also in that blockchain gallery as well.  This piece is only 1/1 editions whereas the latter is collectively the same price but split into only 25 editions(great for a joint investment buy).  

KnownOrigin.io is an ethereum cryptocurrency art gallery bootstrapping decentralized blockchain technology to rarify artworks.  For the first time in computing history we are now able to make digital art rare.  Further artworks by yours truly are on the wall to your right as well.  Enjoy and have a Pepsi!
ETH donations to SadPlanet Virtual is much appreciated!

# Ｂｅｃｏｍｉｎｇ░Ｆｒｅｓｈ
List Price $50,000

In a collaboration with Sascha Bailey, the curator of Blockchain Art Exchange, RobnessロブネスCyberpop has released 'Becoming Fresh.'  A fine art collage piece that is part of a series of collage works that stem from elements of Los Angeles West Coast nostalgia, the doom and gloom of a failing Hollywood, the possibilities of a utopian/dystopian future to come and elements of the global Vaporwave and Cyberpunk communities. Robness has culminated these high value masterworks in series he calls "Save Hollywood."  This piece is valued at $50,000 and can be acquired through the Blockchain Art Exchange Gallery through Opensea.  Both Sascha and Robness has interesting pasts, Sascha is the son of great and renowned sixties photographer David Bailey and has carved his own path in the art world, whereas Robness is one of the first artists to see and participate in the blockchain art experiments that gave birth what you see now.  As a part of the very few who have sold RarePepe meme cards over the amounts of $15,000 and above, he was seminal in helping both Sarutobi and Spells of Genesis test their first games and test ideas of tokenizing the first ever game assets.  He also has authored 2 books, is a singer, dj, graphic designer, blockchain enthusiast, clothing brand creator etc.  

This piece is sold as a one of kind and there will be no other editions.  Currently being sold via the DAI token but arrangements can be made if making a proposition to acquire.

The Death of GrounBEEFtaxi:

As Robness was laying the groundwork for the book 'Memphis Megahertz and the Kansas City Fractal,'
the self proclaimed Bitcoin 'uber-capitalist vaporwave producer' GrounBEEFtaxi died in a speeding
hyperspace crash on the information superhighway.  His music is laid to rest here to enjoy, he
never really got good at mixing and mastering and perhaps was a reason he felt comfortable in
the Vaporwave community.  Anyhow, his music is still on bandcamp and the best
of his material is placed around this lounge for your to enjoy.  He was a son of a bitch but 
I think he made a couple good tracks here and there.  R.I.B.
Portal to GrounBEEFtaxi memorial discography

SadPlanet Vaporwave Virtual Art Gallery(SVVAG)

These art pieces in front of you and placed around here with silver lining
are blockchain rareified artworks that have been placed in SuperRare.co,
KnownOrigin.io and BlockchainArtExchange.com galleries.  A lot of these
works were developed by the curator of SadPlanet Virtual, Robness Cyberpop
but some others are from other notable artists as well.  For example, behind
you towards the rear entrance door there is a piece entitled 'Bonsai Code' by
an artist named Gary Cartlidge which I think is wonderful.  Most of the
other pieces are housed in the SuperRare gallery and we will switch out pieces
here from time to time.  I want to keep this place as f r e s h as we can.
If you have major suggestions on how to make this place better please
go into our telegram room and feel free to tell our curator.  Thank you!
